==English==

===Etymology===
[[Middle English]] ''fairie'', from [[Old French]] ''[[faerie]]'', from ''[[fae]]'', from [[Vulgar Latin]] ''[[Fāta]]'', goddess of fate, from {{L.}} ''[[fātum]]'', fate

===Noun===
'''fairy''' (''plural'' '''[[fairies]]''')

#<!--DefA-->A mythical being, usually small, slim, often with gauzy wings
#<!--DefB-->(''derogatory slang'') A [[male]] [[homosexual]], especially one who is [[effeminate]].

====Synonyms====
*<!--DefA-->(''mythical being''): [[faerie]], [[faery]], [[sprite]]
*<!--DefB-->(''male homosexual''): [[fag]] (''US''), [[faggot]] (''US''), [[poof]] (''UK''), [[queen]]

